      <Member Name="bo_movepathstop" Datatype="Bool">
        <Comment>
          <MultiLanguageText Lang="en-US">Task #5 (2026-05-22): planned-stop / abort request, written by the auto FBs and read by FB_AxisCtrl. While TRUE, FB_AxisCtrl runs MC_GroupStop to decelerate the kinematics group to a halt and end the move job (not resumable - distinct from bo_movepathhalt, which pauses). The auto abort path raises this and waits for output.bo_stopped before the tail reset.</MultiLanguageText>
        </Comment>
      </Member>
      <Member Name="bo_movepathhalt" Datatype="Bool">
        <Comment>
          <MultiLanguageText Lang="en-US">R6 pause/halt request, written by the auto FBs and read by FB_AxisCtrl. While TRUE, FB_AxisCtrl runs MC_GroupInterrupt to halt motion mid-trajectory (axes stay enabled, holding position); on FALSE it runs MC_GroupContinue to resume. Originally a placeholder for LKinCtrl_MC_MovePath.interrupt; reused as the generic pause signal.</MultiLanguageText>
        </Comment>
      </Member>
